Student find goes down a bomb in Irish classroom . An Irish geography teacher who encouraged students to bring geological items into class got a shock when one pupil turned up with a rusty grenade . Students had to be evacuated from the secondary school in Castledermot , County Kildare , on Wednesday after the police and army were called in to deal with the World War One vintage Mills grenade , found in a local field . " It was safe but there was no way of knowing that until it was examined . It was just a shell of a grenade , " an army spokesman said . 
